<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>If you're looking for a foundation with a full-coverage and shine-free formula but that won't budge or settle into fine lines as it wears, there's one budget find you can always count on.</p>

<p>Enter the Lasting Finish 25hr Foundation with Comfort Serum from Rimmel London, which has over 2,000 five-star reviews from people who comment on its coverage and long-lasting finish.</p>

<p>The best part? The number one bestselling foundation is now reduced by 25 per cent on Amazon. Ringing in at £6.74 for a bottle - this is a downright bargain.</p>

<p>Shoppers say the Rimmel London Lasting Finish 25hr Foundation with Comfort Serum is an affordable dupe to higher-end brands and that it will stay in place all. day. long.</p>

<p>The Rimmel London Lasting Finish 25hr Foundation with Comfort Serum has been a cult-favourite for years. The full-coverage formula, which is available in seven shades, boasts an SPF of 20 to help keep you protected from the sun's rays while adding a dose of hydration.</p>

<p>Applied to the skin, the oil-free foundation which has a velvety finish, feels relatively lightweight on but is still opaque enough to cover blemishes and under-eye circles.</p>

<p>Shoppers say it's an affordable dupe to higher-end brands and that it will stay in place all. day. long. It's set to become your new staple.</p>

<p>'Wouldn't use anything else after using this,' one happy customer exclaimed. 'Blends lovely. Feels lovely and lasts all day.'</p>

<p>'This has to be the best foundation colour that goes with my pale skin, it was lightweight with full coverage, and I didn't need to use a lot,' wrote another five-star reviewer. 'It lasted all day even in 31-degree heat outside and being sweaty.'</p>

<p>A third shopper agreed adding: 'My favourite foundation ever. I have oily skin and used to use the Maybelline matte foundation, but this is better. Long-lasting keeps the shine at bay and a great price.'</p>

<p>Now reduced to £6.74, the Rimmel London Lasting Finish 25hr Foundation with Comfort Serum has been a cult-favourite for years</p>

<p>Several shoppers compare the Rimmel London Lasting Finish 25hr Foundation with Comfort Serum to Estée Lauder Double Wear, saying it's a great alternative if you're on a budget.</p>

<p>'Having used Estée Lauder Double Wear for years I was fed up paying so much for my foundation,' one shopper wrote. 'I tried this after reading reviews on Amazon and was not disappointed.</p>

<p>'It smells nice, goes nicely on to my face, and I've received compliments on how clear my skin looks. Plus it's a great price. If your thinking of trying it, do it!'</p>

